docs.abstract: Microsoft eliminated forced arbitration agreements with employees who make sexual harassment claims and is supporting a proposed federal law to ban such agreements.
docs.snippet: Microsoft eliminated forced arbitration agreements with employees who make sexual harassment claims and is supporting a proposed federal law to ban such agreements.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — The wave of sexual harassment claims has toppled powerful men in entertainment, media and politics. Now, it is also creating permanent changes in workplace policy at one giant technology company.

headline.main: Microsoft Moves to End Secrecy in Sexual Harassment Claims
headline.print_headline: Microsoft  Amplifies  The Voices  Of Accusers

byline.original: By Nick Wingfield and Jessica Silver-Greenberg

docs.abstract: While some technology companies used their websites to proclaim support for equal internet access, some of the giants, including Google and Microsoft, were lying low.
docs.snippet: While some technology companies used their websites to proclaim support for equal internet access, some of the giants, including Google and Microsoft, were lying low.
docs.lead_paragraph: Protests to preserve net neutrality, or rules that ensure equal access to the internet, migrated online on Tuesday, with numerous online companies posting calls on their sites for action to stop a vote later this week.

headline.main: Net Neutrality Protests Move Online, Yet Big Tech Is Quiet
headline.print_headline: Tech Giants Quiet as Neutrality Protests Move Online
